<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Make a cross cut at the bottom of the tomatoes, soak in boiling water a couple of minutes, then rinse in fresh water and peel. Cut into eights]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Melt the ghee or oil / butter mixture over medium high heat. Fry the grated ginger, chopped chilies, cumin seeds, mustard seeds until the mustard seeds begin to pop.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Stir in cauliflower, ground coriander, turmeric, salt and stir a coupe of minutes]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the tomatoes, lower heat and cook with a tight fitting lid for 15 - 20 mins, shaking the pan occasionally. The moisture in the tomatoes should be enough to cook the cauliflowers.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Remove the lid and increase the heat. Toss the cauliflower over high heat for a minute or so. Sprinkle garam masala and chopped herbs, and serve]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
